    "direction_from_components": "őł = tan‚ĀĽ¬Ļ(Ay/Ax)",
    "vector_notation": "A = Ax √ģ + Ay ńĶ",
    "pythagorean_truth": "Ax=3, Ay=4 ‚Üí |A|=5 NOT 7. Components combine by Pythagoras not addition.",
    "unit_vectors": "√ģ is unit vector along +x, ńĶ along +y, kŐā along +z",
    "magnitude_invariant": "Changing őł changes Ax and Ay but NOT |A|. The original vector magnitude is preserved.",
    "angle_convention_warning": "If őł from y-axis: Ax=Asinőł, Ay=Acosőł. Formula SWAPS. Always identify reference axis.",
    "dc_pandey_ex5_4": "F=15N at 37¬į from ‚ąíx toward +y: Fx=‚ąí12N, Fy=+9N. Negative component valid.",
    "dc_pandey_ex5_6": "W=10N on 30¬į incline: perpendicular=10cos30¬į=5‚ąö3‚Čą8.66N, parallel=10sin30¬į=5N",
    "dc_pandey_ex5_7": "F=8N at 45¬į: Fx=Fy=8cos45¬į=4‚ąö2‚Čą5.66N. Equal components at 45¬į.",
    "non_perpendicular_axes": "Sine rule used when resolving along non-perpendicular axes. Rare in JEE Main."
  },
  "minimum_viable_understanding": "A vector A at angle őł from x-axis has x-component Ax=Acosőł and y-component Ay=Asinőł, and these reconstruct A exactly via |A|=‚ąö(Ax¬≤+Ay¬≤) ‚ÄĒ never by Ax+Ay.",
